name: Funnel Arch
description:
Introduction

Approach

Follow cairns and well-worn trail. Some scrambling required. Handline or top-belay to get up the nose of the fin may be needed for some.

Descent

From the top anchor either rappel to the arch anchor or walk down with exposure.

Exit

Take the climbers exit down the crack at 38.521,-109.6001 for some additional fun on the way back to the trailhead. Easier than it appears from the top.
